    "content" : "This is a german built 21 window samba. 1966, originally delivered to Finland.\n<br> \n<br> The van was completely stripped and the body restored by JMA Refinishers in original colours (Velvet Green). Harry Harpics did an IRS conversion and all of the running gear which look fantastic.\n<br> \n<br> The interior was done by Delilahs with original split bench and a pair of Rusty Lee Rock n Roll beds that are arranged facing each other like a Devon. The cabinets were custom built. It has the original Golde sun roof with a new cover.\n<br> \n<br> This is a truley lovely van. There are a few odd jobs to finish her off... I was thinking about upgrading the steering to R&amp;P so did not restore the original box. And I have not hung curtains as yet (I blame the wife!)\n<br> \n<br> I am asking Â£60,000 or near offer. \n<br> \n<br> Thanks for looking\n<br> \n<br> Kevin\n<br> 07969 078 155",
