    "content" : "Hi Steve\n<br> If you email me on 07969 078 155 I can send a video walking around. \n<br> \n<br> The engine was supplied by Harry Harpics (who also did an IRS conversion using Beetle 1303 gearbox) and is very nice indeed. It drives very well but it is not fast as I wanted it fairly standard.\n<br> There is no rust. It was totally stripped, any bad metal was replaced and a bare metal respray. \n<br> \n<br> The bad points:\n<br> I mentioned the steering is not great (but it never is) as I was thinking of a rack and pinion upgrade that I never got around to. \n<br> The steering wheel is not restored. I did not fit a new one as I am told they are not as good... but I have not found somebody who restores them.\n<br> One front screen is cracked - but I have a spare.\n<br> There are no curtains nor visors - I just never got around to it.\n<br> I have not got the table yet.\n<br> \n<br> I have owned the bus for about 8 years. The resto was finished a couple of years ago and has hardly been used since, \n<br> \n<br> I am based in Essex near Basildon... its about 10 minutes from the M25. \n<br> \n<br> Thanks \n<br> Kevin",
